<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Geoffrey Goodfellow</ENAMEX> , who dropped out of high school back in <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">the 1970s</ENAMEX> to manage a computer network at a <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">California</ENAMEX> research firm , says : `` Old network hands have started to turn off the network because they do n't have time to wade through the muck . ''
